{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "In a multicenter study, Jones et al.",
    "used 715,343 radiographs across 16 anatomic regions and an ensemble of 10 convolutional neural networks for fracture detection, with a mean area under the curve (AUC) above 0.98 in half of the anatomic sites [9].",
    "developed a two-step approach to first detect the anatomic region among 20 different bones and thereafter to classify fractures, with an accuracy of 90% [42].",
    "Regarding fracture classification, Chung et al.",
    "developed a proximal humerus fracture classification model based on Neer criteria using antero-posterior radiographs [12]."
  ],
